<p>GDP growth: 1.3% GDP: $15,604bn (PPP: $15,604bn) Inflation: 2.1% Population: 316.3m GDP per head: $49,340 (PPP: $49,340)</p>

<p>Campaigning for presidential and congressional elections in November will dominate every waking hour of the political calendar. Barack Obama will be running for a second term amid the highest unemployment rate in 30 years, placing him in a hugely vulnerable position. But his electoral chances will depend as much on the nature of his Republican opponent as on his own record: if the Republicans nominate a candidate on the tea-party fringe, they will lose. If they select someone more moderate, Mr Obama is in trouble. The economy will also be in trouble, though it should—just—avoid another recession. </p>

